## Scroll Panel

Use `dropdownMaxHeight` to cap long option lists. When the panel opens, the selected item scrolls into view.

### Select (scrollable dropdown)
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="SelectSelectScrollableDropdownDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import type { TxSelectValue } from '@talex-touch/tuffex'
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const value = ref<TxSelectValue>('queue-12')
  const queues = Array.from({ length: 24 }).map((_, index) => {
    const id = index + 1
    return { value: `queue-${id}`, label: `Processing queue ${id}` }
  })
  </script>

  <template>
    <TuffSelect v-model="value" placeholder="Select queue" :dropdown-max-height="180">
      <TuffSelectItem
        v-for="queue in queues"
        :key="queue.value"
        :value="queue.value"
        :label="queue.label"
      />
    </TuffSelect>
  </template>
---
:::

## Interaction Contract

- `TuffSelect` owns a single primitive `string | number` value by default. Empty state is represented by `''`.
- In `multiple` mode, `TuffSelect` owns `Array<string | number>`, renders selected values as tags, toggles options on click, and keeps the dropdown open.
- `options` can contain plain options or grouped options. Plain options use `{ value, label, disabled? }`; grouped options use `{ label, disabled?, options }`.
- `TuffSelectItem` registers its value and label with the parent select; when `label` is omitted, slot text is used, then the raw value.
- Clicking the trigger toggles the dropdown in non-editable mode. In `editable` or `remote` mode, focusing the trigger opens the dropdown and the trigger text becomes editable.
- Picking an enabled option emits `update:modelValue` and `change`, updates the selected label, and closes the dropdown.
- Disabled selects close the dropdown and block trigger/option interaction. Disabled items remain visible but do not emit updates.
- `searchable` filters registered option labels locally through the panel search input. It is ignored for editable/remote filtering.
- `remote` mode clears child local filtering and emits `search` from input text only while the dropdown is open; use `searchDebounce` to delay requests.
- `allowCreate` only creates `{ value, label }` from the current input and emits `create`; append created options to your host `options` source when they should appear in the list.
- When a value is provided before items mount, the select resolves the display label after options register. Numeric strings and numbers compare by numeric value when both are finite.

## API

### TuffSelect Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|------|
| `modelValue` / `v-model` | `string \| number \| Array<string \| number>` | `''` | Selected value; array in `multiple` mode. |
| `placeholder` | `string` | `'请选择'` | Placeholder shown in the trigger input when no label is selected. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Disables the trigger, closes the dropdown, and blocks option selection. |
| `multiple` | `boolean` | `false` | Enables multi-select tag mode. |
| `status` | `'default' \| 'error' \| 'warning'` | `'default'` | Validation border state. |
| `eager` | `boolean` | `true` | Eagerly mounts the Popover panel for stable slot option registration. |
| `options` | `TxSelectOptionLike[]` | `[]` | Plain or grouped option data. |
| `maxTagCount` | `number` | - | Maximum visible selected tags; extra tags render as `+ N ...`. |
| `maxTagTextLength` | `number` | - | Maximum visible tag label length before truncation. |
| `searchable` | `boolean` | `false` | Shows an internal search input for local option filtering when the select is not editable. |
| `searchPlaceholder` | `string` | `'Search'` | Placeholder for the internal local search input. |
| `editable` | `boolean` | `false` | Uses the trigger input as editable search text and opens on focus. |
| `remote` | `boolean` | `false` | Enables editable remote mode and emits `search` while the dropdown is open. |
| `allowCreate` | `boolean` | `false` | Allows creating a new option from the current input. |
| `createText` | `string` | `'Add item'` | Default create action label. |
| `loading` | `boolean` | `false` | Shows the loading state. |
| `loadingText` | `string` | `'Loading...'` | Default loading text. |
| `emptyText` | `string` | `'No results'` | Default empty text. |
| `searchDebounce` | `number` | `0` | Remote search debounce in milliseconds. |
| `dropdownMaxHeight` | `number` | `280` | Maximum dropdown list height in pixels. |
| `dropdownOffset` | `number` | `6` | Popover offset from the trigger. |
| `contentPadding` | `number` | `8` | Inner dropdown content spacing. |
| `optionPadding` | `number` | `0` | Horizontal option inset compensation. |
| `animation` | `BaseAnchorAnimationOptions` | - | Animation configuration forwarded to Popover / BaseAnchor. |
| `duration` | `number` | `120` | Dropdown animation duration in milliseconds. |
| `panelVariant` | `'solid' \| 'dashed' \| 'plain'` | `'solid'` | Popover panel surface variant. |
| `panelBackground` | `'pure' \| 'mask' \| 'blur' \| 'glass' \| 'refraction'` | `'refraction'` | Popover panel background style. |
| `panelShadow` | `'none' \| 'soft' \| 'medium'` | `'soft'` | Popover panel shadow strength. |
| `panelRadius` | `number` | `18` | Popover panel corner radius. |
| `panelPadding` | `number` | `0` | Popover panel inner padding. |
| `panelCard` | `BaseAnchorPanelCardProps` | - | Optional panel card overrides forwarded to the Popover panel. |

### TuffSelect Events

| Event | Params | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `update:modelValue` | `(value: string \| number \| Array<string \| number>)` | Emitted with the selected value; array in `multiple` mode. |
| `change` | `(value: string \| number \| Array<string \| number>)` | Emitted with the same value after enabled selection or clear. |
| `search` | `(query: string)` | Emitted in remote mode while the dropdown is open and editable text changes. |
| `create` | `(option: TxSelectOption)` | Emitted when `allowCreate` creates an option from input. |

### TuffSelect Slots

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `default` | - | Legacy `TuffSelectItem` option declarations. |
| `option` | `{ option, selected }` | Custom option content in `options` mode. |
| `tag` | `{ option, remove }` | Custom selected tag content. |
| `group` | `{ group }` | Custom group heading content. |
| `loading` | - | Custom loading state. |
| `empty` | - | Custom empty state. |
| `footer` | `{ query, canCreate, create }` | Custom dropdown footer content. |

### TuffSelectItem Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|------|
| `value` | `string \| number` | - | Primitive option value written to the parent select when picked. |
| `label` | `string` | - | Fallback visible label and registered selected-label text. Slot text is used when omitted. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Prevents picking this option while leaving it visible in the dropdown. |

### Exposed Methods

| Method | Description |
|------|------|
| `open()` | Opens the dropdown. |
| `close()` | Closes the dropdown. |
| `toggle()` | Toggles the dropdown. |
| `focus()` | Focuses the trigger input. |
| `blur()` | Blurs the trigger input. |
| `clear()` | Clears the value and selected label; emits `''` in single mode and `[]` in multiple mode. |

